    "summary": "Repair contributor PR #99917 by adding focused regression tests for shortenText when maxLen is zero or negative, then run the normal changed gate before merge preflight.",
    "pr_title": "fix(commands): guard shortenText against non-positive maxLen",
    "pr_body": "## What Problem This Solves\nRepairs #99917 so the existing contributor fix includes regression coverage for the new non-positive maxLen contract in shortenText.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nClawSweeper found the source guard useful but blocked merge because maxLen=0 and negative values were not covered by focused tests. Add assertions in src/commands/text-format.test.ts that prove shortenText returns an empty string for those limits while preserving existing truncation behavior.\n\n## User Impact\nCommand/status output shortening no longer returns an ellipsis that exceeds a zero or negative requested limit. Attribution remains with @Super-Cabbage and source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/99917.\n\n## Evidence\n- Current main source inspection: src/commands/text-format.ts appends an ellipsis for over-limit strings without a non-positive guard.\n- Current main tests cover fit/truncation/multibyte behavior but not maxLen<=0.\n- Required validation after repair: pnpm test src/commands/text-format.test.ts --run; pnpm check:changed.",
    "likely_files": [
      "src/commands/text-format.test.ts",
      "src/commands/text-format.ts"
    ],
    "validation_commands": [
      "pnpm test src/commands/text-format.test.ts --run",
      "pnpm check:changed"
    ],
    "credit_notes": [
      "Preserve #99917 as the source PR and keep @Super-Cabbage credited as the contributor for the guard against non-positive shortenText limits.",
      "This is a repair_contributor_branch path because maintainer_can_modify=true and the branch is narrow; do not replace the PR."
    ],
